Evolution of Pain (The Nightmare Scenario)

Imagine the early internet without network protocols.

You build a system where:

Computer A sends data as HELLO123

Computer B expects DATA:HELLO

Computer C sends binary packets

Computer D expects structured messages

Result:

💥 Total chaos

Problems that happen:

Machines can't understand each other

Data arrives in wrong order

Some packets are lost

No standard way to send messages

Servers and clients can't communicate reliably

For example:

You open a website.

Instead of loading the page:

Error: Unknown data format

Or a video call:

Audio arrives after video
Packets lost
Connection unstable

This chaos is why network protocols were invented.

Your notes also describe this idea:

Network protocols define rules for data exchange so devices can understand each other. 



